  <H2>Hopf Bifurcation: From Excitable to Oscillatory</H2>

  <Body>One of the most important features of the FHN model is its ability to transition between excitable and oscillatory regimes. This transition occurs via a Hopf bifurcation—a qualitative change where a stable fixed point loses stability and a limit cycle is born.</Body>

  <Body>The Hopf bifurcation occurs when the eigenvalues of the Jacobian cross the imaginary axis. At this critical point:</Body>
  <Body>• The trace of J equals zero: tr(J) = 0</Body>
  <Body>• The determinant remains positive: det(J) &gt; 0</Body>
  <Body>• Eigenvalues are purely imaginary: λ = ±iω</Body>

  <Body>In the FHN model, increasing the applied current I shifts the v-nullcline upward, moving the fixed point along the w-nullcline. When the fixed point reaches the middle branch of the cubic (where the slope is steep enough), the system becomes unstable and oscillations emerge.</Body>

  <Code lang="python">
import numpy as np
from scipy.integrate import odeint
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def demonstrate_hopf_bifurcation():
    """Show transition from excitable to oscillatory regime."""
    alpha, K, c, b = 0.1, 1.0, 3.0, 0.01

    # Different applied currents: excitable vs oscillatory
    I_values = [0.0, 0.02, 0.05]
    regime_names = ['Excitable (I=0)', 'Near bifurcation (I=0.02)', 'Oscillatory (I=0.05)']

    t = np.linspace(0, 500, 5000)

    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 3, figsize=(15, 8))

    for col, (I, name) in enumerate(zip(I_values, regime_names)):
        # Perturb from approximate fixed point
        v0 = 0.1  # slight perturbation
        w0 = v0 / c
        initial = [v0, w0]

        solution = odeint(fhn_system, initial, t, args=(alpha, K, I, c, b))
        v_traj, w_traj = solution[:, 0], solution[:, 1]

        # Time series
        axes[0, col].plot(t, v_traj, 'b-', linewidth=0.8)
        axes[0, col].set_xlabel('Time')
        axes[0, col].set_ylabel('v')
        axes[0, col].set_title(f'{name}\nTime Series')
        axes[0, col].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

        # Phase plane
        v_range = np.linspace(-0.5, 1.5, 200)
        w_vnull = -v_range * (v_range - alpha) * (v_range - 1) + I/K
        w_wnull = v_range / c

        axes[1, col].plot(v_range, w_vnull, 'k--', alpha=0.5, label='v-nullcline')
        axes[1, col].plot(v_range, w_wnull, 'k:', alpha=0.5, label='w-nullcline')
        axes[1, col].plot(v_traj, w_traj, 'b-', linewidth=0.5, alpha=0.7)
        axes[1, col].set_xlabel('v')
        axes[1, col].set_ylabel('w')
        axes[1, col].set_title('Phase Plane')
        axes[1, col].set_xlim(-0.5, 1.5)
        axes[1, col].set_ylim(-0.1, 0.4)
        axes[1, col].grid(True, alpha=0.3)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

demonstrate_hopf_bifurcation()
  </Code>

