  <H2>Practical Applications and Extensions</H2>

  <Body>The FHN model serves as a prototype for excitable media and has applications beyond single neurons:</Body>

  <Body>• Cardiac tissue: The FHN model describes action potential propagation in heart muscle</Body>
  <Body>• Spatial patterns: Extended FHN equations produce traveling waves and spiral waves</Body>
  <Body>• Network dynamics: Coupled FHN oscillators model synchronization phenomena</Body>
  <Body>• Control theory: The simple structure enables analytical treatment of neural control problems</Body>

  <Body>Extensions of the FHN model include:</Body>
  <Body>• Noise terms for stochastic excitability</Body>
  <Body>• Spatial diffusion terms for wave propagation</Body>
  <Body>• Coupling terms for oscillator networks</Body>

